WHO

Usage: ^gWHO [sort] [hired] [pker] [immortal] [mortal]^n

Lists the people currently in the game.  Some people may be invisible.
Command-line options can be used to limit the listing.  The parameters
can be specified on the command-line in any order.

sort       Sorts the players by status
hired      Lists only running players (those with their "hired" flag on)
ooc        Lists those players who can hear the OOC channel
pker       Lists only those players with their "pker" flags on
hardcore   Lists those who have chosen to play in hardcore mode
immortal   Lists those whose status exceeds or is builder
mortal     Lists the players who have not (or do not want to) achieved
           legendary status
newbie     Lists all players with less than 26TKE

^c< 10P 10M > who sort quest^n

Lists the questing characters by status.

^WSee Also: TITLE^n
